### ============================================
### STEP 1: Login to Get Token ✅
### ============================================
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "itmanager@rim.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### ============================================
### STEP 2: Get All Incidents ✅
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ⚠️ NOTE: Check response to see actual incident IDs!
### Example: If you see "id": 4, use 4 in following requests

### ============================================
### STEP 3: Get Incident by ID ✅
### ============================================
### ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Use actual ID from STEP 2!

### Get Incident ID 4 (from screenshot)
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### STEP 4: Create New Incident ✅
### ============================================
### ⚠️ CRITICAL: DO NOT include "notes" field in create!
### Notes can be added later via PATCH

### Minimal Create (Required fields only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Network Connection Down",
  "description": "Store network completely down, affecting all POS terminals",
  "storeId": 7,
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "category": "NETWORK"
}

###

### Create with Equipment ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Printer Not Working",
  "description": "Receipt printer not printing, needs maintenance",
  "storeId": 7,
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "category": "HARDWARE",
  "equipmentId": 4
}

###

### Create Low Priority
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Software Update Request",
  "description": "Request to update POS software to latest version",
  "storeId": 7,
  "priority": "LOW",
  "category": "SOFTWARE"
}

### ============================================
### STEP 5: Update Incident (Add Notes) ✅
### ============================================
### ⚠️ Use actual incident ID from create response

### Add Notes to Incident
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Technician dispatched. ETA 30 minutes. Router replacement needed."
}

###

### Update Title and Description
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Network Connection Down - Updated",
  "description": "Network issue identified as router malfunction"
}

###

### Update Priority
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "priority": "CRITICAL"
}

### ============================================
### STEP 6: Assign Incident to Technician ✅
### ============================================

### Assign to Technician ID 3
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003/assign
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assignedToId": 3
}

### ============================================
### STEP 7: Resolve Incident ✅
### ============================================

### Resolve with Resolution Text
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003/resolve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resolution": "Replaced faulty router. Network connection restored. All POS terminals back online.",
  "resolvedById": 3
}

### ============================================
### STEP 8: Get Incident Statistics ✅
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents/statistics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### STEP 9: Pagination & Filters ✅
### ============================================

### Get with Pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Filter by Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?status=OPEN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?status=IN_PROGRESS
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?status=RESOLVED
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Filter by Priority
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?priority=HIGH
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?priority=MEDIUM
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Filter by Store
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?storeId=7
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Multiple Filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?status=OPEN&priority=HIGH
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### STEP 10: Search ✅
### ============================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/incidents?search=network
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### COMPLETE WORKFLOW TEST
### ============================================

### 1. Create New Incident
# @name createIncident
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "CCTV Camera Offline",
  "description": "Security camera #3 not responding",
  "storeId": 7,
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "category": "HARDWARE"
}

###

### 2. Get Incident ID from response above, then update notes
### Replace INC-2025-XXXX with actual incident code
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Technician contacted. Will check on-site."
}

###

### 3. Assign to Technician
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003/assign
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assignedToId": 3
}

###

### 4. Update Progress
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Technician on-site. Checking camera power supply."
}

###

### 5. Resolve Incident
POST {{baseUrl}}/incidents/INC-2025-0003/resolve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resolution": "Power cable disconnected. Reconnected and camera back online.",
  "resolvedById": 3
}

